Ask HN: Need guidance to transition from Tech/Programming to Product Management
text:
It's been increasingly hard for me to transition to a Product Management from Sr. Data Scientist role. I've tried platforms like pay-only-after-you-get-hired platforms but no success (not even interview calls). My fulltime company has Project Management & Product Development Management roles, but the responsibilities are majorly people management and finishing a project within a timeline rather than scoping out features, launching new product, involve in sales & growth strategy.

About me: (On a work visa in the US)

- 11+ coding experience; 6+ Data Science side. Most of my Data Science side (full-time) involves in pitching the products to the business and building products.

- Have launched & marketed multiple SaaS & Chrome Apps since 2017. Only 3 survived and ongoing; one man show

- Grown a platform to 110K+ registrations in a year, with 2.5K DAU

- One of my chrome extensions is selected as Google's favorite

My interest towards product started for 2 reasons

- 1. Feeling too much of coding in my life (professional & side projects)

- 2. I'm finding more happiness in growing the product than building a app

Any suggestions are greatly appreciated.

Ask HN: AirPods Pro 2 causing tinnutus?
text:
I've used different kinds of headphones, including AirPods Max, for hours, the whole day.

However, my tinnitus has started after about a month I've purchased AirPods Pro 2.

There are many similar reports on the internet.

My volume level is set to minimum (75db) and I don't listen to music often, however my ears have started to ring on a constant basis like I've been to loud concert recently.

Have you noticed something similar with your pair of APP2?

Show HN: AI course creator for micro-learning
text: Our team (MCG) has built an AI powered solution that creates a complete, highly accurate & ready-to-share mini-course. We believe this feature is making the lives of coaches, training providers and online course creators a lot more easier. Because for those people getting started with content creation is a big issue and time creates a big hesitancy. Besides, LMS tools (which are great for macro-course building) is a bit overkill for what they need, like lead generation, onboarding, micro-learning dripping, and so on. Our solution will generate a full course with a small description, and after a few edits like adding images, quizzes, editing appearance, the course will be ready to share. We are using Open AI’s GPT3 as our source. Looking forward to your feedback.
